  1. Get help

How to Get Help

Thank you for your interest and for using our products!

Our projects are constantly being improved and supported, striving to provide the highest possible quality. We mainly focus on helping developers of complex enterprise systems, as the systems they create are meant to be used for decades. Our goal is to provide stable and long living code, as well as maximize compatibility wherever we can.

If any questions arise while working with our products, or if you would like to share your ideas on how we could improve, please make a post on stackoverflow.com.

If you would like to help the project, we recommend checking out the “How to contribute” section, to familiarize yourself with coding and documentation standards adopted by our team.

If you’ve found a bug, report it on the GitHub repository’s bug tracking page. For any other questions, feel free to send us a message.

Additionally, our team specializes in helping organizations make the switch to microservices and DevOps. If you are interested in such a service, be sure to visit our business website.
